msgid "Industrial agriculture is characterized by agricultural areas larger than 5 ha that tend to be homogeneous and often consist of a single crop. In some cases, agriculture may be more varied, consisting of many fields closely packed together. Therefore, large areas consisting of many small fields cultivated at the same time are also considered industrial agriculture under the definition."
